{"data":[{"name":"82:1","price":" 1. When the heaven is cleft asunder.","arabic":"إِذَا ٱلسَّمَآءُ ٱنفَطَرَتۡ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5830,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"idhā al-samāu infaṭarat ","translations":["When","the sky","(is) cleft asunder","(1)"],"transliterationArr":["idhā","al-samāu","infaṭarat",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,420],[2,420,3289],[3,3289,4824]]}},{"name":"82:2","price":" 2. And when the stars have fallen and scattered.","arabic":"وَإِذَا ٱلۡكَوَاكِبُ ٱنتَثَرَتۡ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5831,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-idhā al-kawākibu intatharat ","translations":["And when","the stars","scatter","(2)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-idhā","al-kawākibu","intatharat",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,710],[2,710,1980],[3,1980,4585]]}},{"name":"82:3","price":" 3. And when the seas are burst forth.","arabic":"وَإِذَا ٱلۡبِحَارُ فُجِّرَتۡ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5832,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-idhā al-biḥāru fujjirat ","translations":["And when","the seas","are made to gush forth","(3)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-idhā","al-biḥāru","fujjirat",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,590],[2,590,1680],[3,1680,2645]]}},{"name":"82:4","price":" 4. And when the graves are turned upside down (and bring out their contents)","arabic":"وَإِذَا ٱلۡقُبُورُ بُعۡثِرَتۡ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5833,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-idhā al-qubūru buʿ'thirat ","translations":["And when","the graves","are overturned","(4)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-idhā","al-qubūru","buʿ'thirat",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,690],[2,690,1820],[3,1820,3305]]}},{"name":"82:5","price":" 5. (Then) a person will know what he has sent forward and (what he has) left behind (of good or bad deeds).","arabic":"عَلِمَتۡ نَفۡسٞ مَّا قَدَّمَتۡ وَأَخَّرَتۡ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5834,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"ʿalimat nafsun mā qaddamat wa-akharat ","translations":["Will know","a soul","what","it has sent forth","and left behind","(5)"],"transliterationArr":["ʿalimat","nafsun","mā","qaddamat","wa-akharat",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,910],[2,910,1520],[3,1520,2720],[4,2720,3820],[5,3820,5645]]}},{"name":"82:6","price":" 6. O man! What has made you careless about your Lord, the Most Generous?","arabic":"يَٰٓأَيُّهَا ٱلۡإِنسَٰنُ مَا غَرَّكَ بِرَبِّكَ ٱلۡكَرِيمِ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5835,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"yāayyuhā al-insānu mā gharraka birabbika al-karīmi ","translations":["O","man","What","has deceived you","concerning your Lord","the Most Noble","(6)"],"transliterationArr":["yāayyuhā","al-insānu","mā","gharraka","birabbika","al-karīmi",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2660],[2,2660,4540],[3,4540,4720],[4,4720,5850],[5,5850,6860],[6,6860,9425]]}},{"name":"82:7","price":" 7. Who created you, fashioned you perfectly, and gave you due proportion.","arabic":"ٱلَّذِي خَلَقَكَ فَسَوَّىٰكَ فَعَدَلَكَ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5836,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"alladhī khalaqaka fasawwāka faʿadalaka ","translations":["Who","created you","then fashioned you","then balanced you","(7)"],"transliterationArr":["alladhī","khalaqaka","fasawwāka","faʿadalaka",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,940],[2,940,1850],[3,1850,3170],[4,3170,4525]]}},{"name":"82:8","price":" 8. In whatever form He willed, He put you together.","arabic":"فِيٓ أَيِّ صُورَةٖ مَّا شَآءَ رَكَّبَكَ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5837,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"fī ayyi ṣūratin mā shāa rakkabaka ","translations":["In","whatever","form","what","He willed","He assembled you","(8)"],"transliterationArr":["fī","ayyi","ṣūratin","mā","shāa","rakkabaka",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1580],[2,1580,2180],[3,2180,3130],[4,3130,4100],[5,4100,5580],[6,5580,7115]]}},{"name":"82:9","price":" 9. Nay! But you deny Ad-Dîn (i.e. the Day of Recompense).","arabic":"كَلَّا بَلۡ تُكَذِّبُونَ بِٱلدِّينِ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5838,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"kallā bal tukadhibūna bil-dīni ","translations":["Nay","But","you deny","the Judgment","(9)"],"transliterationArr":["kallā","bal","tukadhibūna","bil-dīni",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,850],[2,850,1240],[3,1240,2710],[4,2710,5555]]}},{"name":"82:10","price":" 10. But verily, over you (are appointed angels in charge of mankind) to watch you,[1]","arabic":"وَإِنَّ عَلَيۡكُمۡ لَحَٰفِظِينَ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5839,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"(V.82:10) Narrated Abu Hurairah رضي الله عنه: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said: \"Angels come (to you) in succession by night and day, and all of them get together at the time of the Fajr and ‘Asr prayers. Then those who have stayed with you overnight, ascend unto Allâh, Who asks them (and He knows the answer better than they): \"How have you left My slaves?\" They reply, \"We left them while they were praying and we came to them while they were praying\". The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم added: \"If anyone of you says Amîn (during the prayer at the end of the recitation of Sûrat Al-Fâtihah), and the angels in heaven say the same, and the two sayings coincide, all his past sins will be forgiven\". (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.4, Hadith No.446).","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-inna ʿalaykum laḥāfiẓīna ","translations":["And indeed","over you","(are) surely guardians","(10)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-inna","ʿalaykum","laḥāfiẓīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1320],[2,1320,2330],[3,2330,5395]]}},{"name":"82:11","price":" 11. Kirâman (Honourable) Kâtibîn writing down (your deeds),[2]","arabic":"كِرَامٗا كَٰتِبِينَ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5840,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"(V.82:11) Whoever intended to do a good deed or a bad deed.\nNarrated Ibn ‘Abbâs رضي الله عنهما: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم narrating about his Lord عز وجل said, \"Allâh ordered (the angels appointed over you) that the good and the bad deeds be written, and He then showed (the way) how (to write). If somebody intends to do a good deed and he does not do it, then Allâh will write for him a full good deed (in his account with Him); and if he intends to do a good deed and actually does it, then Allâh will write for him (in his account) with Him (its reward equal) from ten to seven hundred times, to many more times; and if somebody intends to do a bad deed and he does not do it, then Allâh will write a full good deed (in his account) with Him, and if he intends to do it (a bad deed) and actually does it, then Allâh will write one bad deed (in his account).\" (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.8, Hadith No.498).","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"kirāman kātibīna ","translations":["Noble","recording","(11)"],"transliterationArr":["kirāman","kātibīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1530],[2,1530,4255]]}},{"name":"82:12","price":" 12. They know all that you do.","arabic":"يَعۡلَمُونَ مَا تَفۡعَلُونَ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5841,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"yaʿlamūna mā tafʿalūna ","translations":["They know","whatever","you do","(12)"],"transliterationArr":["yaʿlamūna","mā","tafʿalūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1130],[2,1130,1620],[3,1620,4205]]}},{"name":"82:13","price":" 13. Verily, the Abrâr (the pious believers of Islamic Monotheism) will be in Delight (Paradise);","arabic":"إِنَّ ٱلۡأَبۡرَارَ لَفِي نَعِيمٖ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5842,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"inna al-abrāra lafī naʿīmin ","translations":["Indeed","the righteous","(will be) surely in","bliss","(13)"],"transliterationArr":["inna","al-abrāra","lafī","naʿīmin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1070],[2,1070,2440],[3,2440,3090],[4,3090,5225]]}},{"name":"82:14","price":" 14. And verily, the Fujjâr (the wicked, disbelievers, polytheists, sinners and evil-doers) will be in the blazing Fire (Hell),","arabic":"وَإِنَّ ٱلۡفُجَّارَ لَفِي جَحِيمٖ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5843,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-inna al-fujāra lafī jaḥīmin ","translations":["And indeed","the wicked","(will be) surely in","Hellfire","(14)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-inna","al-fujāra","lafī","jaḥīmin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1170],[2,1170,2560],[3,2560,3150],[4,3150,5545]]}},{"name":"82:15","price":" 15. Therein they will enter, and taste its burning flame on the Day of Recompense,","arabic":"يَصۡلَوۡنَهَا يَوۡمَ ٱلدِّينِ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5844,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"yaṣlawnahā yawma al-dīni ","translations":["They will burn (in) it","(on the) Day","(of) the Judgment","(15)"],"transliterationArr":["yaṣlawnahā","yawma","al-dīni",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1490],[2,1490,2080],[3,2080,4515]]}},{"name":"82:16","price":" 16. And they (Al-Fujjâr) will not be absent therefrom.","arabic":"وَمَا هُمۡ عَنۡهَا بِغَآئِبِينَ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5845,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wamā hum ʿanhā bighāibīna ","translations":["And not","they","from it","(will be) absent","(16)"],"transliterationArr":["wamā","hum","ʿanhā","bighāibīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,650],[2,650,1050],[3,1050,1870],[4,1870,6635]]}},{"name":"82:17","price":" 17. And what will make you know what the Day of Recompense is?","arabic":"وَمَآ أَدۡرَىٰكَ مَا يَوۡمُ ٱلدِّينِ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5846,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wamā adrāka mā yawmu al-dīni ","translations":["And what","can make you know","what","(is the) Day","(of) the Judgment","(17)"],"transliterationArr":["wamā","adrāka","mā","yawmu","al-dīni",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1240],[2,1240,2680],[3,2680,3140],[4,3140,3750],[5,3750,6275]]}},{"name":"82:18","price":" 18. Again, what will make you know what the Day of Recompense is?","arabic":"ثُمَّ مَآ أَدۡرَىٰكَ مَا يَوۡمُ ٱلدِّينِ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5847,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"thumma mā adrāka mā yawmu al-dīni ","translations":["Then","what","can make you know","what","(is the) Day","(of) the Judgment","(18)"],"transliterationArr":["thumma","mā","adrāka","mā","yawmu","al-dīni",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,860],[2,860,2270],[3,2270,3410],[4,3410,3870],[5,3870,4500],[6,4500,7165]]}},{"name":"82:19","price":" 19. (It will be) the Day when no person shall have power (to do) anything for another, and the Decision, that Day, will be (wholly) with Allâh.","arabic":"يَوۡمَ لَا تَمۡلِكُ نَفۡسٞ لِّنَفۡسٖ شَيۡـٔٗاۖ وَٱلۡأَمۡرُ يَوۡمَئِذٖ لِّلَّهِ","category":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar"],"ayahNumber":5848,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"yawma lā tamliku nafsun linafsin shayan wal-amru yawma-idhin lillahi ","translations":["(The) Day","not","will have power","a soul","for a soul","anything","and the Command","that Day","(will be) with Allah","(19)"],"transliterationArr":["yawma","lā","tamliku","nafsun","linafsin","shayan","wal-amru","yawma-idhin","lillahi",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,590],[2,590,1090],[3,1090,2000],[4,2000,2670],[5,2670,4200],[6,4200,5910],[7,5910,7520],[8,7520,8790],[9,8790,12415]]}}],"chapter":["82 (Al-Infitar)","Al-Infitar","Surah Al-Infitar","Chapter Al-Infitar","Infitar","Surah Infitar","Chapter Infitar","Al Infitar","Surah Al Infitar","Chapter Al Infitar","Surah 82","Chapter 82","The Cleaving","الإنفطار"],"version":{"key":"english_hilali_khan","direction":"ltr","language_iso_code":"en","version":"1.1.0","last_update":1577394000,"title":"English Translation - Hilali and Khan","description":"Translation of the Quran meanings into English by Taqi-ud-Din Al-Hilali and Muhsen Khan"}}